BIRD ANALYSES

# load bird data
df_birds <- read.csv("VFAvianSurveyData5-Jan-2023.csv")
# if group size missing, assume 1 individual
df_birds$GroupSize[df_birds$GroupSize == -999] <- 1

# format SurveyDate column as a date
df_birds$SurveyDate <- dmy(df_birds$SurveyDate)

# add column for month
df_birds$Month <- as.factor(month(df_birds$SurveyDate))

# add column for year
df_birds$Year <- as.factor(year(df_birds$SurveyDate))

# VFzone remove c or t
df_birds$Pair <- as.numeric(substr(df_birds$VFzone, 1, nchar(df_birds$VFzone)-1))
#add column if burned in year of survey date, yes or no
df_birds$BurnedInYear[df_birds$Year == "2022" & df_birds$Burn2022 == "yes"] <- "yes"
df_birds$BurnedInYear[df_birds$Year == "2023" & df_birds$Burn2023 == "yes"] <- "yes"
df_birds$BurnedInYear[df_birds$Year == "2022" & df_birds$Burn2022 == "no"] <- "no"
df_birds$BurnedInYear[df_birds$Year == "2023" & df_birds$Burn2023 == "no"] <- "no"
#### summarize species richness by year ####

# summarize number of species in control vs treatment each year and month
df_allbirdrichness <- df_birds %>%
  group_by(Year, Control_or_Treatment, Pair, Month, BurnedInYear) %>%
  summarize(Richness = length(unique(Species)))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year', 'Control_or_Treatment', 'Pair',
## 'Month'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#make df with only focal species
df_grassland <- df_birds[df_birds$Focal == 'TRUE', ]

# summarize number of species in control vs treatment each year
df_grasslandbirdrichness <- df_grassland %>%
  group_by(Year, Control_or_Treatment, Pair, Month, BurnedInYear) %>%
  summarize(Richness = length(unique(Species)))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year', 'Control_or_Treatment', 'Pair',
## 'Month'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#glm without random effect of pair but including burn & interactions
grasslandspeciesrichness_nopair <- glm(Richness ~ Control_or_Treatment + Year*Control_or_Treatment + Month + BurnedInYear + BurnedInYear*Control_or_Treatment, data=df_grasslandbirdrichness, family=poisson)

summary(grasslandspeciesrichness_nopair)

#rewrite abundance for each focal species #change 0 counts #Grasshopper Sparrow, Henslow’s Sparrow, Eastern Meadowlark, Dickcissel, Upland Sandpiper, Common Nighthawk, Brownheaded Cowbird, Northern Bobwhite, Mourning Dove #GRSP, HESP, EAME, DICK, UPSA, CONI, BHCO, NOBO, MODO

# summarize count data by survey and species
birdabundance <- df_birds %>%
  group_by(SurveyEventID,Year, Control_or_Treatment, BurnedInYear, Month, Pair, Species) %>%
  summarize(Count = sum(GroupSize))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'SurveyEventID', 'Year',
## 'Control_or_Treatment', 'BurnedInYear', 'Month', 'Pair'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.
# create a data frame with all combinations of surveys and species
all_surveysspecies <- expand.grid(SurveyEventID = unique(df_birds$SurveyEventID),
            Species = unique(df_birds$Species))

# join surveys with survey info
all_surveysspecies <- left_join(all_surveysspecies, distinct(birdabundance[,1:6]), 
                                by = "SurveyEventID")

# join count data with surveys
birdabundance <- merge(all_surveysspecies, birdabundance, all = TRUE)

# fill in 0 counts
birdabundance[is.na(birdabundance)] <- 0
# split out GRSP
dfgrsp <- birdabundance[birdabundance$Species == 'GRSP', ]

#grsp abundance glm without random effect of pair but including burn & interactions
grspabundancenopair <- glm(Count ~ Control_or_Treatment + Year*Control_or_Treatment + Month + BurnedInYear + BurnedInYear*Control_or_Treatment, data=dfgrsp, family=poisson)

summary(grspabundancenopair)

# load vegetation data
df_veg <- read.csv("AllUplandVegMeasurements_1Dec2023.csv")
# format SurveyDate column as a date
df_veg$Date <- dmy(df_veg$Date)

# add column for month
df_veg$Month <- as.factor(month(df_veg$Date))

# add column for year
df_veg$Year <- as.factor(year(df_veg$Date))

# create time variable
df_veg$Time <- ifelse(df_veg$Month == "5" & df_veg$Year == "2022", 1,
                                 ifelse(df_veg$Month == "6" & df_veg$Year == "2022", 2,
                                        ifelse(df_veg$Month == "7" & df_veg$Year == "2022", 3,
                                               ifelse(df_veg$Month == "5" & df_veg$Year == "2023", 4,
                                                      ifelse(df_veg$Month == "6" & df_veg$Year == "2023", 5,6)))))

# VFzone remove c or t
df_veg$Pair <- as.numeric(substr(df_veg$VFzone, 1, nchar(df_veg$VFzone)-1))
#add column if burned in year of survey date, yes or no
df_veg$BurnedInYear[df_veg$Year == "2022" & df_veg$Burn2022 == "yes"] <- "yes"
df_veg$BurnedInYear[df_veg$Year == "2023" & df_veg$Burn2023 == "yes"] <- "yes"
df_veg$BurnedInYear[df_veg$Year == "2022" & df_veg$Burn2022 == "no"] <- "no"
df_veg$BurnedInYear[df_veg$Year == "2023" & df_veg$Burn2023 == "no"] <- "no"
#remove -999 values from center and edge robel measurements
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$CenterRobel_N != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$CenterRobel_S != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$CenterRobel_E != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$CenterRobel_W != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$EdgeRobel_N != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$EdgeRobel_S != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$EdgeRobel_E != -999,]
df_veg <- df_veg[df_veg$EdgeRobel_W != -999,]
#calculate mean veg height across 8 measurements for each point
df_veg$VegHeight <- rowMeans(df_veg[, 10:17])
#average vegetation height
groupeddfveg <- df_veg %>%
  group_by(Year, Control_or_Treatment, Pair, Month, BurnedInYear, CenterVsEdge) %>%
   summarize(AverageHeight = mean(VegHeight))
